# tetris-python

Python port of the original Go Tetris implementation, organized using a
Ports and Adapters (Hexagonal) architecture.

## Architecture

- `src/tetris/domain`: pure game rules, entities, and board logic
- `src/tetris/application`: use-case orchestration and port interfaces
- `src/tetris/adapters`: terminal/curses input-output implementations

This keeps gameplay rules independent from terminal I/O so alternate adapters
(web, pygame, tests, bots) can be added without changing the domain model.

## Run

```bash
python -m pip install -e .
python -m tetris
```

or

```bash
python -m pip install -e .
python -m tetris.cli
```

Controls:

- Left/Right arrows: move block
- Up arrow: rotate clockwise
- Down arrow: rotate counterclockwise
- Space: hard drop
- q: quit

## Test

```bash
pytest
```
